Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Technician Vancouver , BC Description Little Flower Academy is seeking applicants for the position of Library Technician. This is a part-time position (approximately 21 hours/week) commencing September 1, 2024.Responsibilities:Help to foster a warm, inclusive school library environment for students and staff.Assist patrons with item circulation and library account management.Catalogue and physically process new materials.Help to facilitate extracurricular activities and library programs.Work alongside the librarian to help patrons with readers’ advisory and reference questions.Promote the collection by creating displays and booklists.Aid librarian with collection maintenance tasks such as weeding and inventory.Order supplies for the library.Support the Catholic character of the school.Other related duties as required.Qualifications:Diploma from a recognized Library Technician program or equivalent.Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.Experience using Destiny ILS or equivalent.Ability to work both independently and as part of a team.Attributes:Personable.Intrinsically motivated.Methodical and detail-oriented.Adaptable and flexible.Compensation:$28.00 - $31.00 per hour. Comprehensive benefits package.How to Apply:Please send CV and supporting documentation to the attention of Diane Little, Head of School at headofschool@lfabc.org. Applications are accepted until Friday, May 10, 2024.We would like to thank all applicants in advance for submitting their CVs. Please note, only those candidates chosen to continue through the selection process will be contacted.For more information on our school’s mission, culture, and programs, please visit www.lfabc.org. Compensation $28 - $31 per hour. Comprehensive benefits package. Closes: 10 May, 2024 Little Flower Academy Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
