Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Acquisitions Clerk Brandon , MB Description Posting also available on Brandon University Employment Opportunities page: https://www.brandonu.ca/jobs/Completed resumés and cover letters are accepted by e-mail to hr@brandonu.ca. Please quote the Job Vacancy Number in the email subject line.Applications are to be received by: 4:30 pm on May 6, 2024Job Vacancy Number: 2024 – 05 (75)Employee Group: MGEUClassification: Clerk 6, Library Acquisitions ClerkDepartment: Library ServicesType of Position: Full-Time, RegularHours of Work: 35 hours per weekWage or Salary: $28.87 per hourStart Date: June 3, 2024Probation or Trial Period: Minimum of 6 months to a 12 month maximumDate Issued: April 29, 2024Duties and Responsibilities:This position is responsible for all activities in the daily operation of the Library Acquisitions Department including, but not limited to: coordination and processing of library resource licenses, procurement, and receipt of both print and electronic library resources; managing the library acquisitions budget and endowment funds; providing statistical data and projections related to the acquisitions budget and spending; and other related duties as assigned.Required Qualifications and Experience:The successful candidate must possess a 2-3 years’ post-secondary diploma or equivalent. Diplomas in library and information technology, business administration, accounting, or supply management are preferred. Three (3) years of related academic library experience or a comparable combination of education and experience is required.The ideal candidate must demonstrate: strong research and critical thinking skills; knowledge of budget management, purchasing, and the procure-to-pay process; experience working with and implementing policy and procedural documents; a high degree of initiative; a keen attention to detail; excellent organizational, interpersonal, and oral and written communication skills; strong computer skills and knowledge of Microsoft Office. Knowledge of various library programs and databases, such as Ex Libris’ Alma is an asset. Statistical analysis and financial reporting experience are an asset. The successful candidate must be able to work with limited supervision, work positively, harmoniously, collaboratively, and effectively as a part of a team in a rapidly changing environment, and deal effectively with both colleagues, including Faculty, and external vendors.*NOTE*Skill based testing may be required. This position is subject to a Child Abuse Registry Check and Criminal Record Check. The successful candidate will be responsible for any service charges incurred. These checks must be submitted in accordance with the Policy in order to maintain employment.Brandon University is committed to equity, welcomes diversity, and hires on the basis of merit. All qualified individuals who may contribute to the diversification of the University, especially women, persons with disabilities, Indigenous persons, racialized persons, and persons of all sexual orientations and genders are encouraged to apply. Canadian citizens and permanent residents are given priority. Evidence of citizenship must be provided.We are committed to providing an inclusive and barrier-free work environment. This starts with the hiring process. Should you require an accommodation during any phase of the recruitment process, contact HR at hr@brandonu.ca. All information received related to an accommodation is kept confidential. To ensure this employment opportunity is accessible to all interested individuals, this posting is available in an alternate format upon request. Compensation $28.87 per hour Closes: 6 May, 2024 Brandon University Brandon , MB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
