Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Technician Regina , SK Description Full-time Permanent Position Available The Saskatchewan Health Authority (SHA) Library, Regina location, invites applications for a full-time permanent Library Technician position from individuals who are looking to work in an exciting and progressive organization. The successful applicant will join a dynamic award-winning team providing library services across the provincial Saskatchewan Health Authority. The SHA Library provides access to approximately 1,200 electronic books, 26,000 plus full-text journals and a core suite of electronic databases. The majority of services are provided virtually through the SHA Library’s website. Additional services are provided at staffed physical locations in Regina at the Regina General Hospital, Pasqua Hospital and the Wascana Rehabilitation Centre. Responsibilities Reporting to the Manager of Knowledge Management &amp; Library Services, the Library Technician will work as part of a team delivering information services to a variety of health care professionals and a broad range of students and physicians from across the Health Authority.The Library Technician will work within Insignia, the Library’s new cloud-based system. Extensive work in LibGuides and DB/Textworks is involved.Duties may include processing interlibrary loans, performing document delivery, updating the Library’s website, distributing current awareness services, upkeep of physical libraries, customer service and basic client support, daily library system/resource/mobile, and equipment troubleshooting, processing invoices for payment, and all related record-keeping and documentation. Qualifications: Education: Library and Information Technology Diploma Knowledge, Skills and Abilities: Advanced computer skills Detail-oriented, meticulous Superior interpersonal, organizational and communication skills Ability to prioritize work, adapt to changing workloads with excellent organizational skills Ability to work independently The Saskatchewan Health Authority offers competitive salaries and a comprehensive benefits package.Those who thrive working in a fast-paced, stimulating environment will be interested in joining our team.Interested applicants are invited to submit a cover letter, resume and three references in confidence, quoting Job Number RQ-00025803, by May 13, 2024 to: Email: jobs@rqhealth.ca Employment Services Saskatchewan Health Authority 2180 23rd Ave. Regina, SKS4S 0A5 Applicants considered for interviews will be contacted. www.saskhealthauthority.ca https://saskhealthauthority.libguides.com/home Compensation Rate of Pay: 22.60 - 24.21 Closes: 13 May, 2024 Saskatchewan Health Authority Library Regina , SK Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
