Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Vernon Campus Librarian Kelowna , BC Description OKANAGAN COLLEGEOkanagan College transforms lives and communities. We are one of Canada's leading colleges. We create outstanding educational experiences for our learners, both students and employees. We work and learn in a welcoming and caring culture. We are a catalyst for change through collaboration with our learners and partners. We serve, lead and anticipate the social, economic and environmental needs of communities.Position Title:Vernon Campus LibrarianCompetition Number:C002782Division/Portfolio:Library ServicesDepartment/Program:LibraryCampus/Centre:VernonYour Opportunity:Under the general direction of the Director of Library Services, is responsible for coordinating and participating in the delivery of Vernon campus Library reference and instruction services, supervising Vernon Library support staff, and representing the Library in working with campus administrators and support units and in campus committee participation. Other duties include collection development, liaison with one or more instructional departments, participation in Library committees, collaboration with other Librarians, professional development, service, and may include scholarly activity.Education and Experience:Minimum qualification is a degree from an accredited Master’s program in library and information studiesExperience in the provision of library instruction and reference services.Experience assisting library users with both print and electronic resources, including creating instructional materials in a variety of formats.Recent experience in an academic library is preferred.Supervisory experience is preferred.Collection development experience is preferred.Experience coordinating initiatives and integrating concepts related to equity, diversity, inclusion and social justice (EDISJ), accessibility, and/or Indigenization in a library setting is an asset.Experience with planning and project management is an asset.Functions and Duties:1. Coordinates Library public services (reference, instruction, circulation, etc.) on the Vernon campus2. Supervises Vernon Library support staff.3. Provides reference services, in person, by email, and in a real-time virtual environment.4. Prepares and delivers instruction to students, in person and in a virtual environment.5. Prepares guides and tutorials to research and to the use of Library collections and services, using a variety of media and formats.6. Acts as liaison to one or more instructional departments as appropriate to ensure that Library collections and services meet instructional and student needs.7. Participates in the development of the library collection by working with the Collections and Metadata Librarian and departmental Library representatives to plan for resource needs and to select books, media and other materials.8. Contributes to planning and development of Library policies and procedures by participating in the Library Management Committee9. Represents the Library in working with campus administrators and support units and in campus committee participation and in campus activities.10. Engages in professional development activity intended to promote subject area and technical competence in librarianship and information science.11. Engages in service activities that support the College and/or the profession and/or the community.12. If requested and approved, may engage in scholarly activity, which may include scholarship, research and creative activity.13. Performs other related Librarian duties as assigned.14. Some evening and weekend work may be required.Skills and Abilities:· Familiar with, and supportive of, new and emerging technologies in library services and instructional settings· Strong oral and written communication skills· Ability to facilitate communication and connections among students and faculty· Ability to work independently, and as part of a team, to assist in the delivery of library servicesAppointment Type:Faculty - Full-time ContinuingAppointment Start Date:06/17/2024Schedule:35 hours/week; some evenings and weekend work may be required from time to time.Annual Salary/Hourly Rate:Salary range $71,846 to $115,129 with normal starting salary between $78,872 and $85,897 annually*, dependent on relevant education and experience. *Note: Part-time Term and summer appointments subject to adjustment factors as per the collective agreementSpecial Instructions to Applicants:For more information about this posting, including the complete job description, please contact Roen Janyk, Interim Director of Library Services (rjanyk@okanagan.bc.ca) or Eva Gavaris, Library Department Chair (egavaris@okanagan.bc.ca).For more information about the library or our EDISJ statement, visit our website: https://www.okanagan.bc.ca/library/about-oc-librar...Posting Opening Date:04/22/2024Posting Closing Date:05/12/2024APPLICATIONS:To apply for this position, please go to our employment site: https://www.employmentopportunities.okanagan.bc.ca and complete an on-line application. All applications must be submitted through our employment site to be considered.Okanagan College is committed to increasing the equitable and inclusive participation of marginalized people in all aspects of college life. We welcome and encourage applications from Indigenous Peoples, Black People, members of racialized groups/visible minorities, people with disabilities and people with diverse gender identities or expressions. People with disabilities who anticipate needing accommodations for any part of the application process may contact, in confidence, AccessibilityHR@okanagan.bc.ca Compensation Salary range $71,846 to $115,129 with normal starting salary between $78,872 and $85,897 annually*, dependent on relevant education and experience. *Note: Part-time Term and summer appointments subject to adjustment factors as per the collective agreement Closes: 12 May, 2024 Okanagan College Kelowna , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
