Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Coordinator, Maker &amp; Emerging Technology Caledon , ON Description Job Title: Coordinator, Maker and Emerging TechnologyClosing Date: May 5, 2024 12:00 PMCaledon Public Library is a hub for discovery, innovation and inspiration. We nurture connections, collaboration and creativity and are situated within a dynamic municipality that successfully balances urban, rural and agricultural communities. With seven branches that serve as the cornerstones to the community, connecting people to information and each other is what we do!We are seeking a dynamic, energetic individual with proven maker and tinkerer experience, as well as excellent customer service, programming and library skills.The OpportunityReporting directly to the Supervisor, Community and Creation, as part of the Information Services department, this role is responsible for the development, execution and support of makerspace programs and events, as well as engaging the community with innovative opportunities for learning, creation and discovery. This role will also be responsible for providing reference and information services, customer service and community outreach. As the Coordinator, Maker &amp; Emerging Technology, your responsibilities will be, but not limited to:Work with technology users with varying levels of experience in one-on-one sessions and group settingsActively assist customers of all ages in the makerspace with a variety of machinery and software including but not limited to 3D printers, laser engraver/cutters, Cricut, heat press, embroidery machineActively assist customers of all ages in the recording studio, supporting their use of recording, photography and video equipmentUnder the guidance of the Supervisor, Community and Creation, helps to prepare or obtain related maker and technology equipment training materialsProvide technology training and assistance to local businesses and entrepreneursDemonstrate makerspace technology and recording studio equipment to staff, empowering and supporting staff in the delivery of related services.In consultation with the IT department, maintain relevant equipment and softwareActively seek out and recommend new trends in maker and creator technology, both digital and analogStay current with emerging technologiesManage and maintain makerspace equipment, ensuring all equipment and accessories are present and in good working conditionMaintain a supply inventory and advise Supervisor when restocking is requiredThe Ideal CandidateWe are seeking a candidate with maker knowledge normally acquired through a post-secondary degree/diploma in art, design or technology, or a closely related field. Our ideal candidate has two years of public experience as well as two years in a customer-focused setting. We are seeking people with excellent communication and customer service skills as well as superior interpersonal skills including the ability to work effectively in a team environment and foster effective working relationships.This position offers a salary range of $70,059.31 - $84,576.06 plus a competitive benefit package.Notwithstanding the above, candidates who do not fulfill all of our requirements may be considered in a Development Status capacity. Satisfactory passing of a vulnerable sector check, and proof of qualifications will be required of any successful candidate(s) for this position.The Town is an equal opportunity employer that is committed to an inclusive and barrier-free workplace. If your application requires accommodation, please contact Human Resources at (905) 584-2272 Ext. 4738.How To ApplyTo learn more about employment with the Town of Caledon and to apply for this exciting and challenging opportunity, visit: www.caledon.ca/careersIf needed and upon request, this document can be made available in an alternative format. Compensation $70,059.31 - $84,576.06 Closes: 5 May, 2024 Caledon Public Library Caledon , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
