quotes and RFPs. Public Relations and Communications: Direct the ongoing promotion of the Library and its services to the general public, represent the Library at community functions and Council meetings and maintain relationships with library partners and collaborators.Library Board Support: Attend Board and Committee meetings, report regularly to the Board on library activities, prepare reports as directed by the Board and/or as required by municipal, provincial, or federal authorities. Prepare Board information packages and ensure timely distribution of reports and information. RequirementsMaster of Library and Information Science (MLIS)Education and training related to bookkeeping (QuickBooks), HR and FOIP are assets3 - 5 years experience in public library services 3 - 5 years experience in management and supervision Excellent computer skills, including Microsoft Office 365, internet and social media Excellent research skills Excellent skills in math, statistics, and reporting Excellent oral and written communication in English. French is an asset Valid driver’s license Excellent public relations and leadership skillsWhat We OfferAn opportunity to help shape the future of library services in MorinvilleA permanent, full-time position with a targeted start date of August, 2024A competitive salary starting at $75,00015 paid vacation daysDays off in lieu of overtimeFull benefits package Enrollment in the Local Authorities Pension Plan (LAPP)To apply for this opportunity, send a resume and cover letter to board@morinvillelibrary.ca by May 3, 2024. The Morinville Community Library appreciates all applicants, but only candidates chosen for interviews will be contacted. Compensation Starting at $75,000 Closes: 3 May, 2024 Morinville Community Library Morinville , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
