Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Technician I (18 Months Contract - Maternity Leave Coverage) Vancouver , BC Description Since 1936 Columbia College has offered quality educational programs designed to prepare students for university admission. These programs include a University Transfer Program fully integrated into the BC Transfer System and a Secondary Program Certified by the Province of British Columbia. Thousands of Canadian and international students have progressed through Columbia’s programs to successful Canadian universities.OPPORTUNITY: The Library is a dynamic partner in our students' educational journey. Our mission is to create a positive learning environment and support student success. Our competitive pay and teamwork ethos make us a favoured employer for library professionals seeking fulfilling work in an upbeat environment. The successful candidate will actively support student learning, guided by a student-centered approach and a strong belief in the value of education. Columbia College Library is seeking a full time Library Technician I to join the Library Team. This position will begin in May 2024 and end in November 2025. KEY RESPONSIBILITIES: Circulate library materials (charging, discharging, renewals, holds) Assist patrons with library computers, copiers, and printers. Assist patrons with locating library materials. Demonstrate use of library website and online catalogue Provide citation and reference assistance in-person or remotely. Under the supervision of the Library Technician 2, catalogue materials or perform catalogue maintenance and upgrading tasks. Provide technical support for electronic resources such as databases and ebooks. Provide training and day-to-day supervision to student employees. Maintain stack and study area organization and tidiness or delegate such tasks to student employees. Assist with collection development and acquisition. Perform materials processing, inventory, de-accessioning Produce book displays, social media, outreach, and programs, or participate in these activities or delegate to student employees. Create and upgrade LibGuides and library website content. Participate in Library planning; proactively propose improvements to services, processes and direction. Supports the Indigenization and EDI activities of the Library and College Other duties as assigned. QUALIFICATIONS: A Library Technician diploma is required. Undergraduate degree preferred. At least 1 year of related work experience. SKILLS &amp; ABILITIES: Knowledge of library circulation services and procedures Experience using an Integrated Library System Extensive working experience with Microsoft Office suite, including Access, Excel, Word, Teams, and Sharepoint. Excellent interpersonal and written/verbal communication skills. Friendly and approachable, with a customer-service orientation. Able to exercise good judgment. Adaptable, flexible, and a team-player. Able to work independently with minimal supervision. Knowledge of International Students and the challenges they face is an asset. COMPENSATION: In addition to working with an inclusive, progressive group of people, we offer a competitive salary based on qualifications and experience. This position’s hourly gross salary is $28.29. APPLICATION PROCEDURE: Please submit your application, including a cover letter and resume, through our portal https://www.columbiacollege.ca/careers/ Please note that filling out the entire profile is not mandatory to upload the required resume and cover letter to the platform. For additional information about the application process, please check Columbia College Application Process Application Deadline: May 7, 2024 At Columbia College, we foster a culture of equity, diversity and inclusion. The College invites and encourages applications from all qualified individuals, including groups traditionally underrepresented in employment, who may contribute to the further diversification of our Institution. We thank all applicants for their interest in the position; only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $28.29/hour Closes: 7 May, 2024 Columbia College Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
